      • locked

        public final User locked(java.lang.Boolean value)
        Sets the locked flag of the User.

        Locking a user is a special operation in openfire due to its maintained by a flag in a specific database table.
        The flag exists only once at a certain time or is vanished. if the flag exists and the end date of the flag is either null or in the future the user account is locked

        Parameters:
        value - true if the User account is locked; otherwise false.
        Allowed object is Boolean.
        Returns:
        the User to allow method chaining.
        Possible object is User.
